Macedonians are preparing to vote in a referendum on EU and NATO membership, provided the name of the country is changed.
The agreement to rename the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia into the Republic of Northern Macedonia was reached on 17 June as a result of long negotiations with neighbouring Greece, which refused to recognize the right of its northern neighbour to be called Macedonia as an attempt on the Greek province of the same name and Greek history.
Lupko Petkovski, political scientist: "Thanks to this agreement Macedonia or Northern Macedonia gets the right to a better future, hope for social changes.
And Greece will entrench the right to its past.
There are no ideal agreements.
They arise from difficult compromises and cannot make absolutely everyone happy".
The ruling Social Democrats, led by Prime Minister Zoran Zaev, are in favor of renaming the country.
Against - the conservative opposition and President Gheorghe Ivanov.
According to journalist Tsvetina Chilimanov, Macedonia does not make sense to join the EU - it is enough to have a partnership with it: "Many of those who do not like the agreement, believe that the current socialist government led by Zaev imposed from outside in order to change the name of the country.
But this decision will have negative consequences.
First of all, loss of sovereignty.
It is obvious that there are countries that would not like Macedonia to remain one of the sovereign countries in the Balkans".
FEI Dulgheri, Euronews: "The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia faces the biggest challenge in its history.
The country is at a crossroads.
The choices Macedonia's citizens make will determine the future not only of the Balkans, but of Europe as a whole".
RF Ministry of Finance forecasts ruble exchange rate for 17 years ahead
The Ministry of Finance of Russia expects a gradual depreciation of the ruble - up to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025, according to the forecast, the ruble exchange rate will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles, and in the next five years - 73.9 rubles.
The agency notes that these figures are the nominal rate.
The real effective exchange rate (an indicator that takes into account changes in the exchange rates of countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assure.
As for inflation, until 2020 it will be 3.5%, and then it will stabilize at about 4%, according to the Ministry of Finance.
