Peskov answered a question about possible support for Serbia on Kosovo
Russian President Dmitry Peskov's spokesman believes that it is premature to say whether Russia will provide assistance to Serbia after the escalation in Kosovo.
According to him, negotiations between the leaders of the two countries should first take place.
The representative of the Kremlin told about it to journalists of radio station "Says Moscow" on Sunday, September 30.
On September 29, Serbian resident Alexander Vucic said that he intends to discuss the situation in Kosovo with Russian President Vladimir Putin at the next meeting in Moscow on October 2.
The Serbian leader also planned to ask for Moscow's support in the current situation, specifying that military assistance in this case is out of the question.
Vucic noted that he would like to preserve peace in the region and intends to do everything necessary for this.
Earlier that day, it was reported that the President of Serbia had ordered the country's armed forces to be put on high alert.
